  "description": "Viktor Adolf Fredriksson was a Swedish elementary school inspector, born on June 23, 1892 in Nå-runga, Älvsborg County. He was married to Alice Bernsten and had three children. He passed the non-commissioned officer exam at the Göta Artillery Regiment in 1912 and the elementary school teacher exam in 1919. He attended a psychology course at Gothenburg University in 1928, and went on study trips to Denmark, Norway, Germany and Switzerland from 1930-1941. He worked as a collaborator for Goteborgs-Posten from 1913-1919 and was employed as an elementary school teacher from 1919. He became a regular teacher in 1921, a supervisor teacher in 1926 and head teacher in 1933. He served as an elementary school inspector in the Gothenburg region from 1942. He was a press ombudsman for the Swedish National Elementary School Teachers' Association between 1925-1933 and served as a board member from 1928-1933. He was a member of the board of directors for the Swedish National Association for the Care of Mentally Handicapped Children from 1930-1946, serving as chairman in 1945-1946. He was also a member of the board of Stretered's School Home from 1930-1939 and served as chairman in 1939. He was a member of the Gothenburg Children's Welfare Committee since 1940 and the 40-year school inquiry. He was a member of the board of the Children's Day Association from 1935-1942 and a member of the church council since 1936, as well as a member of the board at the Upper Secondary School from 1940-1941. He wrote articles for school and daily press and was the editor for the Swedish National Elementary School Teachers' History."
